  <Subject Subject_ID="300179495">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300232876</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>law enforcement vessels [300232876], utility and service vessels [300232858], watercraft by function [300232728], watercraft by specific type [300219289], watercraft [300042940], vehicles (transportation) [300219258], Transportation Vehicles (hierarchy name) [300042929], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Single-masted lightly armed cutters with fire lines built for governments expressly to prevent smuggling and to enforce customs regulations; in use mostly from the late 18th to the early 19th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046680/Kemp, Oxford Companion to Ships and the Sea (1976)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para escampavía de un solo mástil y ligeramente armado, con cuatro líneas de fuego construidas expresamente para que los gobiernos puedan prevenir el contrabando y poner en vigor las regulaciones aduaneras. En uso en su mayor parte desde finales del siglo XVIII hasta principios del siglo XIX.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor lichtbewapende eenmasters met vuurlijnen die speciaal gebouwd zijn om in opdracht van de regering smokkelen te verhinderen en douanevoorschriften te handhaven; werden voornamelijk gebruikt vanaf rond het einde van de 18e tot en met de eerste jaren van de 19e eeuw.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>為政府單位所用、輕武裝且配有火力線的單桅巡邏艇，特別用於防範走私和執行海關法規；主要使用於十八世紀晚期至十九世紀早期。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Leichtbewaffneter Einmaster mit Feuerlinien, gebaut für Regierungen, um insbesondere den Schmuggel zu verhindern und Zollbestimmungen durchzusetzen; vorwiegend vom späten 18. Jahrhundert bis zum frühen 19. Jahrhundert im Einsatz.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
